The 'A-League's 2011â12 season' (known as the Hyundai A-League for sponsorship
reasons) is the seventh season of the Australasian A-League football (soccer)
competition since its establishment in 2004. At the end of the previous season,
the North Queensland Fury were cut from the competition by the governing body,
Football Federation Australia, due to financial reasons.
